My fall and recovery moment from this season. I really appreciate that this performance was filmed. I fell down in my solo that night. I danced 3 out of 3 pieces in this show. I was exhausted but happy! Right before the fall I felt I was going to fly but instead I stepped on my dress and fell on my butt 😂 I remember the feeling of being happy and free. Like the feeling when you let go of your umbrella and just let the rain fall on you. There is no fear or regret only fulfillment and happiness. I’m lucky to be alive and dancing. I loved every moment of this Joyce season. Including this little gem. Enjoy! 
Death/Rebirth solo by @jfreemover

I’m going back to school 💜

Yep, I’m going back to school! I’m so excited to start my MFA at @nyutisch 

It is surreal to be a student again at 38. And I’m starting school on the same day my 3 year old starts her first day of pre-K!

Continuing my education at NYU is another dream come true for me. I came to NYC from China in 2010 with a goal of studying at the @marthagrahamschool independent program for just one year. After that I was supposed to go back to China and continue a career in teaching. But the Graham School offered me a generous scholarship that gave me the opportunity to stay and continue this crazy journey in America. I’ve been with @marthagrahamdance ever since. 

Now 13 years later I’ve been lucky enough to receive a full scholarship from @nyuniversity to participate in a new 2-year interdisciplinary MFA program for dance artists. 

For my Graham fans, I’m not going anywhere! I’m still dancing with Martha Graham Company and you’ll see me on stage in NYC and on some tours. Thanks to support from MGDC and my college advisors, I’ve been able to figure out a schedule works for the company and my class schedule. 

Thank you to my rock Jess, for supporting me on this wild ride and give me the confidence that I can achieve anything that I put my mind to. Thank you to my boss Janet Eilber for your guidance and support from day one. Shout out to the rest of my amazing support system, including my mentors who wrote letters of recommendation. Thank you all for believing in me. I can’t wait to start this next chapter of my journey!
